# .trivyignore — Security CVE suppressions
#
# Policy: every entry MUST document (1) the vulnerability, (2) why we cannot take the fix NOW,
# (3) what compensating control is in place, and (4) what unblocks the fix.
#
# Review cadence: revisit each entry when its blocking dependency constraint is lifted.
# Owner: project maintainer. Reference: docs/plan/TRAIL.md § Deferred Work.

# ── Python transitive dependencies ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8 (langsmith arbitrary server-side file read)
#   Package    : langsmith < 0.8.18 (transitive via langchain)
#   Fix        : langsmith >= 0.8.18
#   Why blocked: langsmith 0.8.18 requires langchain-core >= 1.4.0, which is pre-release only.
#                Upgrading also forces sie-sdk to newer versions that conflict with the stable
#                langchain/numpy/websockets constraint chain. Verified: `uv lock --upgrade-package
#                langsmith` is unsatisfiable.
#   Compensating control: langsmith is only used as an internal tracing client within langchain;
#                         the file-read vector requires an attacker-controlled server config, which
#                         is not reachable from user input in this application.
#   Unblocked by: langchain 1.x stable + langchain-core 1.4.x stable release reaching PyPI, or
#                 sie-sdk dropping the websockets<15 + numpy>=2 constraint (tracked in TRAIL.md).
GHSA-f4xh-w4cj-qxq8

# CVE-2026-4372 (transformers RCE — fix: >= 5.3.0)
# CVE-2026-5241 (transformers arbitrary code execution — fix: >= 5.5.0)
#   Package    : transformers < 5.5.0 (transitive via sentence-transformers)
#   Fix        : transformers >= 5.5.0
#   Why blocked: sentence-transformers 3.x (pinned < 4.0.0 in pyproject.toml line 23) is not
#                compatible with transformers 5.x. Forcing transformers >= 5.0.0 would break
#                CrossEncoder and SentenceTransformer model loading.
#                The < 4.0.0 pin is deliberate: sentence-transformers 4.x introduces a mypy
#                CrossEncoder API change that requires a dedicated ML stack migration slice
#                (see TRAIL.md § Deferred Work: "sentence-transformers v4+").
#   Compensating control: model IDs are validated against a fixed allowlist in
#                         server/core/model_registry.py; arbitrary HuggingFace model IDs from
#                         user input are rejected, narrowing the RCE attack surface significantly.
#   Unblocked by: dedicated ML stack upgrade slice (sentence-transformers >= 4.0, transformers >= 5.5).
CVE-2026-4372
CVE-2026-5241
